        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 1:59PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a broken line of
thunderstorms near Emerson, or 12 miles northeast of Whiteville,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rowan, Penderlea, Carvers, Lisbon, Lagoon, Elkton, Council, Emerson,
Willard, Kelly, Atkinson, and Watha.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 389 and 393.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
